TranslatedAttributes
====================

Translated attributes is a basic plugin that allows you to support multiple languages in your model in simpler way that globalize2 does.

It's dependent on I18n, so use it with Rails edge.

How to use:
-----------
As simple as:

Migration:

  create_table "posts" do |t|
    t.string "title_ar"
    t.string "title_en"
    t.text   "body_en"
    t.text   "body_ar"
  end

Model:

  class Post < ActiveRecord::Base
    translated_attributes :title, :body
  end

View/Controller
  @post = Post.first
  post.title('en') #=> post.title_en
  post.title('ar') #=> post.title_ar
  